The paper deals with privacy preservation in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which involves secure data aggregation and processing. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of data mining techniques, which is related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a randomized data perturbation technique, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
